description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title – Band 4 Nursing Associate&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Base – Leckhampton Lodge - Cheltenham – &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; Assertive Outreach Team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary – &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;£21,089 to £23,761 per annum,&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;pro rata&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours per week – 26.25 (3.5 days / week)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nursing Associate AOT&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This is an exciting opportunity to become part of the Assertive Outreach Team. You will be working with service users who have complex mental health needs, who can be difficult to engage and who require an enhanced level of input from mental health services. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic, motivated; Nursing Associate who can help us support those with complex needs and help to ensure that both their mental and physical health needs are addressed.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The team is based at and will cover the geographical area including Cheltenham, Tewkesbury and the North Cotswolds&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;As a Nursing Associate in the Assertive Outreach Team based at Leckhampton Lodge in Cheltenham you will be responsible for assisting in the delivery of care and services to patients and service users as part of a Mental Health and Social Care Health Service. Under the supervision of registered practitioners assist in the provision of care and treatment to service users in a community setting, in line with the principles of social inclusion and recovery, and the ‘Capabilities for Inclusive Practice’.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To provide support, give time to allocated group of service users with more complex needs and thus promote their recovery and maintain them in their community environment. To assist the care co-ordinator to assess, plan, implement and evaluate individual care plans.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To facilitate access to activities to meet the needs of service users and carers within community settings.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To participate in induction and support of new staff and students and to co-supervise junior staff.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To attend and participate in identified training and the staff appraisal process&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;The qualification, training &amp; experience requirements for the role are underlined in the Job Description/Person Specification.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Closing date: 12&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;th&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; November 2020&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Shortlisting date: 13&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;th&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; November 2020&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Interview date: 27th November &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;2020&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This post requires the post holder to be able to undertake all statutory and mandatory training and post holders must be able to undertake physical interventions. Fitness for physical intervention will be assessed by Occupational Health. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;A valid UK driving licence plus the use of own transport for business purposes is essential. For qualifying staff the Trust has a Lease Car Scheme in place and also offers a popular Salary Sacrifice Car Scheme with our partner Tusker.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;To ensure you fully understand how the Trust, as a Data Controller, will process and store your data please read the attached document ‘Applicant and Staff Privacy Notice’ prior to applying for the role. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Candidates for any staff appointment shall, when making application, disclose in writing to the Trust whether they are related to any governor. Failure to disclose such a relationship may disqualify a candidate and, if appointed, may render him/her liable to dismissal. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
